Description: Body sherd (mended from four fragments) of South Ionian pottery skyphos with handle root at right break; interior glazed black with five narrow added red bands; exterior glazed save for handle zone; two added red lines either side of handle zone; in handle zone band of dotted alternating cross and billet.
Curator's comments: The sherd probably belongs to the same vase as Boston 88.1087 and may join Oxford AN1925.608g, where the number of vertical billets also varies, from one to three.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.881)
